46:22.013 --> 46:25.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On this Independence Day, he
reflects on American
heroes.

46:25.182 --> 46:29.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEBASTIAN JUNGER, Author:
Several years ago,
I spent much of a deployment
with a platoon

46:29.120 --> 46:32.823 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of combat infantry at a remote
outpost called
Restrepo.

46:32.857 --> 46:39.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was named after the medic PFC
Juan Sebastian
Restrepo, who was born in
Colombia, emigrated

46:39.130 --> 46:44.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to America as a child, and died
fighting at
the bottom of a hill in
Afghanistan.

46:44.769 --> 46:48.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was no running water at
Restrepo, no
cooked food, no communication
with the outside

46:48.806 --> 46:53.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
world, and absolutely no
privacy. Mostly,
there was just a lot of combat.
The platoon

46:54.011 --> 46:59.417 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
was in several hundred
firefights that year,
and everyone out there was
almost killed.

46:59.450 --> 47:03.554 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And yet over and over again, I
watched perfectly
ordinary people risk their lives
to keep others

47:03.587 --> 47:08.959 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
safe. No one was more important
than anyone
else, and race, religion, and
politics had

47:08.993 --> 47:14.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
absolutely no relevance at
Restrepo. It was
most profoundly egalitarian
place I have ever

47:14.098 --> 47:15.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
been.

47:16.000 --> 47:20.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every Fourth of July, I like to
think about
men like Private Restrepo and
what this country

47:20.137 --> 47:25.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
must mean to them. Four percent
of our military
aren't even U.S. citizens. And
yet they emigrate

47:25.843 --> 47:30.347 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to our shores, put on a uniform
and fight
and die for us.

47:30.381 --> 47:34.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What is it they are fighting
for? What is
it they are risking death for?
For many, of

47:34.518 --> 47:40.357 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
course, it is economic
opportunity. But that
very economic opportunity is
rooted in the

47:40.391 --> 47:46.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
idea of a just society where
people are judged
on their own merits, rather than
for the sound

47:46.397 --> 47:49.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of their last name or the color
of their skin.

47:49.400 --> 47:55.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that America may exist in
its purest form
on the front lines of our
nation's wars. How

47:55.973 --> 48:03.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sad. How ironic. Soldiers now
return to a
society that is tearing itself
apart along

48:03.047 --> 48:08.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
every possible ethnic and
demographic boundary.
The gap between rich and poor
continues to

48:08.352 --> 48:13.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
widen. Many people live in
racially segregated
communities, and rampage
shootings seem to

48:13.624 --> 48:15.593 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
happen every week or two.

48:15.626 --> 48:20.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To make matters worse, powerful
people in
this country talk with
incredible contempt

48:20.264 --> 48:26.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about, depending on their views,
the president,
the government, the foreign-born
and entire

48:26.971 --> 48:29.540 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
segments of the population.

48:29.573 --> 48:35.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm sorry to say that some of my
fellow Americans
would judge PFC Juan Restrepo
for his country

48:35.946 --> 48:40.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of origin before they got around
to honoring
him for his heroism.

48:40.417 --> 48:45.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't believe that this would
be happening
if people in power in this
country had even

48:45.189 --> 48:50.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
